# __NAME_TITLE__ Entrypoint

This is a doorway into the __NAME_TITLE__ Agent. It carries the request to the
mounted agent contract at `agents/__NAME__.agent.md`; it does not own the work.

Which agent runtime opens this doorway — Codex, Claude Code, Claude Tag, a CLI,
a Slack mention — is the user's choice. Whatever opens it must load the mounted
agent contract first, then the base role (in the pinned protocol), the tenant
overlay, and the selected playbook workflow, and must pass the approval/evidence
gates that live in the playbook.

```yaml
entrypoint:
  mounted_agent: agents/__NAME__.agent.md
  runtime: user_choice
  must_load_first: agents/__NAME__.agent.md
  must_not:
    - act as the reasoning core in place of the mounted agent contract
    - bypass approval or evidence gates
    - store tenant truth here
```
